# SalesFlow CRM — Cursor Rules

Read CLAUDE.md first. This file adds Cursor-specific guidance on top of it.

## Project Type
Full-stack SaaS CRM. React (Vite) frontend + Express.js backend + Prisma/Neon Postgres. Deployed on Render via Docker.

## Stack at a Glance
- Frontend: React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS, @tanstack/react-query, lucide-react, @dnd-kit
- Backend: Node.js, Express, Prisma ORM
- DB: Neon Postgres (serverless)
- AI: Groq (llama-3.3-70b), Anthropic Claude (claude-opus), OpenRouter
- Auth: JWT (access + refresh), Google OAuth, Cloudflare Turnstile
- Real-time: Socket.IO
- Storage: Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible)

## Code Style
- No TypeScript — plain JS throughout
- Tailwind for all styles — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Async/await everywhere — no .then() chains except in Prisma one-liners
- Functional React components only — no class components
- React Query for all server state — no manual useState for API data
- No comments unless the WHY is non-obvious

## File Conventions
- Backend routes: `backend/src/routes/<resource>.routes.js`
- Backend services: `backend/src/services/<resource>.service.js`
- Frontend pages: `frontend/src/pages/<PageName>/index.jsx`
- Frontend shared components: `frontend/src/components/`
- All API calls through `frontend/src/lib/api.js` (axios with auth interceptor)

## Critical Rules
- `isProd = process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'development'` — staging uses NODE_ENV=staging
- All DB queries must include `orgId` for tenant isolation
- `BacklogItem.priority` is always 0–3 — clamp with `Math.max(0, Math.min(3, parseInt(v,10)))`
- Never use Render's `PUT /env-vars` API — it wipes all vars; use individual key endpoint
- Agent-created leads auto-assign to themselves (see `lead.service.js`)
- Groq 429 errors must be retried with the exact wait time parsed from the error message

## Auth Pattern
```js
// Every protected route:
router.use(authenticate);          // sets req.user, req.orgId
router.post('/', requireRole('admin'), handler);  // optional role gate
```

## Adding a New Feature Checklist
1. Add Prisma model/field in `schema.prisma` → run `npx prisma db push`
2. Add service function in `backend/src/services/`
3. Add route in `backend/src/routes/` → mount in `backend/src/index.js`
4. Add API call in `frontend/src/lib/api.js`
5. Build page/component in `frontend/src/pages/`
6. Add route in `frontend/src/App.jsx`
7. Update `docs/USER_MANUAL.md` if user-facing
8. Test on staging before merging to main
